@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>Blazor WASM on GitHub Pages</h1>

<p class="lead">
    A minimal Blazor WebAssembly sample that deploys to GitHub Pages with GitHub Actions.
</p>

<div class="alert alert-info" role="status">
  <strong>New here?</strong>
  Open the <NavLink href="publish-guide">Publishing Guide</NavLink> for step-by-step setup,
  workflow explanation, and GitHub repository settings.
</div>

<h2>What this repo demonstrates</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Automatic publish on push to <code>main</code></li>
    <li>Correct <code>&lt;base href&gt;</code> for project-style GitHub Pages URLs</li>
    <li><code>404.html</code> SPA fallback for client-side routing</li>
    <li><code>.nojekyll</code> so Blazor <code>_framework</code> assets are served</li>
</ul>

<p>
    Workflow file: <code>.github/workflows/dotnet.yaml</code>.
    Live site URL pattern:
    <code>https://&lt;username&gt;.github.io/BlazorGitHubPagesDemo/</code>
</p>
